The paper focuses on object detection in videos using weakly-supervised learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a Long Short-Term Memory network (LSTM), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of action descriptions as supervision, which involves natural language processing (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on a large-scale dataset, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
